domainRuntime() sessionName = String("Customization" + Long(System.currentTimeMillis()).toString()) sessionMBean = findService("SessionManagement", "com.bea.wli.sb.management.configuration.SessionManagementMBean") sessionMBean.createSession(sessionName)
osbConfigurationMBean = findService(String("ALSBConfiguration." + sessionName.toString()), "com.bea.wli.sb.management.configuration.ALSBConfigurationMBean")
fileCounter = 0
for key, configuration in configurations.items(): try: fileCounter = fileCounter + 1 base.logS(base.Info, "Quering for " + configuration["name"] + " service")
query = BusinessServiceQuery() query.setLocalName(configuration["name"]) results = osbConfigurationMBean.getRefs(query) refToModify = results[0]
exported_pom = osbConfigurationMBean.exportReferences(results, False, None)
exportFile = File(sessionName.toString() + str(fileCounter) + ".jar") outputStream = FileOutputStream(exportFile) outputStream.write(exported_pom) outputStream.close()
zipFilePath = Paths.get(exportFile.toURI()) fs = FileSystems.newFileSystem(zipFilePath, None) fileCharset = StandardCharsets.UTF_8
fileToChange = fs.getPath(String("/" + refToModify.getFullName() + ".BusinessService"), []) content = String(Files.readAllBytes(fileToChange), fileCharset) newContent = content.replaceAll(policyToReplace, configuration["policy"]) Files.write(fileToChange, list([newContent]), StandardCharsets.UTF_8, [StandardOpenOption.WRITE, StandardOpenOption.TRUNCATE_EXISTING]) fs.close()
fileToImport = open(sessionName.toString() + str(fileCounter) + ".jar", 'rb') contentToImport = fileToImport.read() bytesToImport = array(contentToImport, 'b') osbConfigurationMBean.uploadJarFile(bytesToImport) jarInfo = osbConfigurationMBean.getImportJarInfo() jarImportPlan = jarInfo.getDefaultImportPlan() jarImportPlan.setPreserveExistingSecurityAndPolicyConfig(False) osbConfigurationMBean.importUploaded(jarImportPlan) fileToImport.close() except Exception: base.logS(base.Warning, 'Failure to change policies for: ' + configuration["name"])
sessionMBean.activateSession(sessionName, "")
standardDomain.addExtender( CustomExtender () )
